PASS | `requirements.txt` — `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n\n### File Map Completeness\n\n| Spec File | Present | Match |\n|-----------|---------|-------|\n| `main.py` | Yes | Exact match |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Yes | All top-level keys present |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Yes | Identity, tools, extra.python.source match |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | Yes | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` with credential validation |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Yes | All 8 parameters with correct schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | Yes | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` with `_invoke` and `execute` |\n| `requirements.txt` | Yes | Correct pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Yes | All present |\n\n### Issues Fixed During Verification\n\n1. **Missing `__init__.py` files** — Added to `integrations/`, `integrations/dify-plugin/`, `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/`, `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/` to enable Python package imports\n2. **Test import errors** — Fixed `test_provider.py` and `test_tool.py` to handle hyphenated directory/module names (`dify-plugin`, `agentcube-code-interpreter.py`) using `sys.path` manipulation and `importlib.util`\n3. **Mock patching target** — Changed tests to patch `CodeInterpreterClient` in the loaded module's namespace (`_agentcube_code_interpreter`) instead of the stub `agentcube_module`\n\n### Verdict\n\n**AR-036 implementation is COMPLETE and COMPLIANT with spec.** All 45 tests pass, all file structures match the design specification, and all API contracts are correctly implemented.","time":{"start":1775884118577,"end":1775884118577}}}
